==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wheatear
<hw>Wheat"ear`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A small European singing bird (<spn>Saxicola ⟦oe⟧nanthe</spn>). The
male is white beneath, bluish gray above, with black wings and a black
stripe through each eye. The tail is black at the tip and in the middle,
but white at the base and on each side. Called also
<altname>checkbird</altname>, <altname>chickell</altname>,
<altname>dykehopper</altname>, <altname>fallow chat</altname>,
<altname>fallow finch</altname>, <altname>stonechat</altname>, and
<altname>whitetail</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wheaten</ent>⟦br⟧
